  <h1>Sales Jobs: High Income Without Technical Skills</h1>

  <p>Sales jobs are one of the best non-technical career options for people who enjoy communication and persuasion. Many sales roles offer performance-based incentives, making them highly rewarding.</p>

  <h2>Types of Sales Jobs</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Retail Sales Executive</li>
    <li>Real Estate Agent</li>
    <li>Insurance Advisor</li>
    <li>Field Sales Representative</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Skills Required</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Communication skills</li>
    <li>Confidence</li>
    <li>Negotiation ability</li>
    <li>Customer understanding</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Why Choose Sales?</h2>
  <p>Sales roles often provide quick growth, flexible earning potential, and opportunities to move into management positions.</p>

  <h2>Where to Find Jobs</h2>
  <p>You can find sales jobs in retail companies, startups, real estate firms, and corporate organizations.</p>

